  "prompt": "Which day can be the first and the last day of a century?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) A century is a period of 100 consecutive years.\n\n2) Centuries are typically counted starting from year 1, not year 0.\n\n3) The first day of a century is January 1st of the first year of that century.\n   \u2022 For example, the 21st century started on January 1st, 2001\n\n4) The last day of a century is December 31st of the 100th year of that century.\n   \u2022 For the 21st century, this would be December 31st, 2100\n\n5) So, the first and last day of a century will always be:\n   \u2022 First day: January 1st\n   \u2022 Last day: December 31st\n\nTherefore, January 1st and December 31st can be the first and last day of a century, respectively.",
